#Approach:
Merge Sorted Array – Three Pointer Approach

Is problem me nums1 ke end me already extra space diya hota hai,
isliye hum merge ko piche se karte hain.

Hum 3 pointers lete hain:
i = nums1 ke valid part ke end par
j = nums2 ke end par
k = nums1 ke total end par

Ab nums1[i] aur nums2[j] ko compare karte hain.
Jo bada hota hai usse nums1[k] par daal dete hain,
phir corresponding pointer aur k ko piche le aate hain.

Agar nums2 ke kuch elements bach jayein,
to unhe nums1 me copy kar dete hain.

Isse in-place merge ho jata hai bina extra array ke.

Time Complexity: O(m + n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public void merge(int[] nums1, int m, int[] nums2, int n) {
        int len = (n+m);
        int gap = (len/2) + (len%2);

        while(gap > 0){
            int left = 0;
            int right = left + gap;

            while(right < len){
                //if left in nums 1 and right in nums2
                if(left < m && right >= m){
                    if(nums1[left] > nums2[right - m]){
                        //swap
                        int temp = nums1[left];
                        nums1[left] = nums2[right-m];
                        nums2[right-m] = temp;
                    }
                }
                // if both left & right are in arr2
                else if(left >= m){
                    if(nums2[left-m] > nums2[right-m]){
                        //swap
                        int temp = nums2[left-m];
                        nums2[left-m] = nums2[right-m];
                        nums2[right-m] = temp;
                    }
                }

                //if both left & right are in arr1
                else{
                    if(nums1[left] > nums1[right]){
                        //swap
                        int temp = nums1[left];
                        nums1[left] = nums1[right];
                        nums1[right] = temp;
                    }
                }
                right++;
                left++;
            }
            if(gap == 1) break;
            gap = (gap/2) + (gap%2);
        }
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            nums1[m + i] = nums2[i];
        }
    }
}
